    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Following review of all 13 credibility factors and the two validation results demonstrating NIH prediction within 8.3% MAE and 94.8% Monte Carlo coverage, the credibility assessment team determined that the model provides sufficient confidence for the VAD hemolysis prediction use case. Residual gaps in model form and input equivalency are noted but deemed acceptable given the conservative safety margins applied to the clinical threshold comparison. Decision: Accepted pending resolution of SQA audit finding within 90 days.",
